                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-102-victim755 t18260914-102-viclabel611"></join>. On the 18th of August I put this looking-glass on a rose-wood table near my door, between nine and ten o'clock in the morning - I went out, and on my return I was informed it had been stolen.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-102-person756">
                  MARY 
                  HAWKINS
               <interp inst="t18260914-102-person756" type="surname" value="HAWKINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-102-person756" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-102-person756" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 18th of August I saw the prisoner standing about Mr. Miller's shop; he took this glass, and was walking away with it; I gave an alarm - he dropped it, and ran off; he was brought back, by the street-keeper, in about three minutes - I am certain of his person.</p>
               <p>
            
